// nodule: std.io
// `std.io` + `serialize` ‚Äî single-consumption IO + canonical serialization (M-514).
//
// Two coupled surfaces over Mycelium's content-addressed value model:
//
// **serialize** ‚Äî project a [`mycelium_core::Value`] to/from a byte or text form:
// - [`serialize::serialize`] / [`serialize::deserialize`] over the RFC-0001 ¬ß4.8
//   self-describing wire form (`[Repr descriptor] ‚Äñ [Meta] ‚Äñ [payload]`,
//   schema-travels-with-data, faithfully round-trippable including `Meta`).
// - [`serialize::to_json`] / [`serialize::from_json`] ‚Äî the **one canonical JSON
//   projection** that `fmt.to_json` (M-533) delegates to (README ¬ß5 seam; FLAGGED
//   ¬ß7-Q1 pending maintainer sign-off).
//
// **io** ‚Äî move bytes over an abstract source/sink:
// - [`io::read_all`] / [`io::read`] / [`io::write`] over [`io::Source`] /
//   [`io::Sink`] ‚Äî affine handles consumed **exactly once** (LR-8 / RFC-0006 ¬ßQ5).
//   Single-consumption is a **type-level invariant** (Rust move semantics), not a
//   runtime convention.
// - [`io::read_value`] ‚Äî the bridge joining io + serialize: deserialize a `Value`
//   directly from a `Source`.
//
// # Honesty crux (twofold, structural)
//
// 1. **Round-trip** ‚Äî `deserialize(serialize(v, f), f) ‚â° v` including `Meta` is a
//    **checked property** (proptest corpus; `Empirical` tag ‚Äî not `Proven`, no
//    checked theorem; VR-5 / spec ¬ß7-Q2).
// 2. **Never-silent** ‚Äî a truncated, malformed, or decode-failed input is an
//    **explicit, located** error (`SerError` / `IoError` carrying a byte offset /
//    field path ‚Äî RFC-0013 I1); **no op returns a partially-filled `Value`** (C1/G2).
//
// # Serialization is a projection, not identity (ADR-003 / C4)
// `serialize`/`to_json` borrow their `&Value` immutably.  The content hash is
// unchanged by serialization.  The round-trip recovers a value with the **same
// content-id**; the projection is not a re-keying.
//
// # Single-consumption (LR-8)
// `read_all` takes [`io::Source`] **by-move** and does not return it ‚Äî the affine
// handle is consumed exactly once.  A double-consume is a **compile-time error**, not
// a runtime check.  Chunked `read` threads the handle linearly; `write` threads
// [`io::Sink`] linearly.
//
// # Declared effects (C6 / RFC-0014 ¬ß4.5)
// - io ops declare the **`io`** effect; chunked `read` additionally declares
//   `alloc(Budget)`.
// - serialize/JSON ops are **pure** (`effects: none`).
//
// # In-memory substrate + OS I/O floor (FLAGGED ¬ß7-Q4 / ¬ß8-Q6)
// The OS I/O floor is deferred to `std-sys` (M-541). This module ships a fully
// testable **in-memory substrate** ([`io::Substrate`] backed by `Vec<u8>`) that
// exercises the affine abstraction without OS facilities. The `std-sys` phylum will
// provide OS-backed constructors for file descriptors and sockets.
//
// # No new trusted code (KC-3 / C5)
// This crate wraps `mycelium-core`'s `serde::{Serialize, Deserialize}` for `Value`
// (landed M-104). No new trusted serialization logic; no `unsafe`.
//
// # Guarantee matrix
// Eight rows ‚Äî one per exported op ‚Äî in [`guarantee_matrix::MATRIX`] (RFC-0016 ¬ß4.5).
// Asserted in tests.
//
// # Design spec
// `docs/spec/stdlib/io.md` (M-514, #155); contract: RFC-0016 ¬ß4.1 (C1‚ÄìC6).
//
// # Open questions (FLAGs from spec ¬ß7)
//
// - **(Q1) One canonical JSON ‚Äî `fmt.to_json` delegation.** `to_json`/`from_json` are
//   proposed as the canonical JSON projection that `fmt` (M-533) delegates to.  Needs
//   maintainer sign-off (spec ¬ß7-Q1 / RFC-0016 ¬ß8-Q1).
//
// - **(Q2) Which round-trip reaches `Proven`.** The `Empirical` tag is the honest
//   maximum for this implementation.  A `Proven` tag would require a checked
//   injectivity/totality theorem over the closed `Repr`/`Meta` grammar (VR-5;
//   spec ¬ß7-Q2).
//
// - **(Q3) The io ‚Üî fs build-on seam.** `fs` (M-528) *builds on* this module's
//   `Source`/`Sink`; the exact path‚Üísubstrate constructor surface is co-design with
//   M-528 (spec ¬ß7-Q3).
//
// - **(Q4) The `wild`/FFI floor for the io half.** Byte movement over a real OS
//   source/sink requires OS facilities ‚Üí `wild`/FFI (ADR-014). Deferred to `std-sys`
//   (M-541; spec ¬ß7-Q4 / RFC-0016 ¬ß8-Q6).
//
// - **(Q5) Format / Budget ergonomics at the call site.** Both `Format` and `Budget`
//   are required-explicit until the per-ring ergonomics pass (M-540; spec ¬ß7-Q5 /
//   RFC-0016 ¬ß8-Q3 tension A).
//
// ## Ambient Representation (RFC-0012 ¬ß8-Q3)
//
// This crate's public API participates in the RFC-0012 ambient-representation contract:
// the representation choice (binary/ternary/dense/VSA) is implicit at the call site but
// always reified, queryable, and EXPLAIN-able ‚Äî never a black box (C3/SC-3).
// [Declared per RFC-0012; direction accepted in DN-07 ¬ß8-Q3; per-ring pass scheduled as M-540.]
//
// **For this crate (Ring 2, Tier B):** I/O is representation-opaque at the byte level ‚Äî
// `Source`/`Sink` move raw bytes without interpreting `Repr`. Callers own the encoding
// choice; the `Format` parameter to serialize ops is always explicit (never inferred from
// context). The serialized form carries the `Repr` descriptor as part of its wire schema
// (RFC-0001 ¬ß4.8 "schema-travels-with-data"), so no silent re-encoding occurs on round-trip.
//
// # Stability (DN-66 freeze, 2026-07-01)
//
// This crate's public API, as documented in `docs/spec/stdlib/io.md` (spec status:
// Accepted (2026-06-20)) and asserted by its guarantee-matrix table, is the **frozen baseline** per
// [DN-66](../../../docs/notes/DN-66-Stdlib-Stable-API-Freeze-And-Rust-Crate-Retirement-Status.md).
// A future breaking change here needs a spec amendment + changelog entry, not a silent edit (G2).
//
// **Unfrozen for the gap-closure window (ADR-045, Accepted 2026-07-10):** this DN-66 freeze is
// lifted per [ADR-045](../../../docs/adr/ADR-045-Kernel-And-Lexicon-Unfreeze-For-Early-Gap-Closure.md)
// for a bounded window; a breaking change here still needs a spec amendment + changelog entry
// (G2), not a silent edit ‚Äî the window closes per the ADR-045 ¬ß2.4 re-freeze conditions, bound by
// the DN-99 residual worklist.
// It remains the RFC-0031 D6 differential-oracle reference; no `.myc` port of this module exists yet, so the D6 retirement trigger has not fired and no item here is `#[deprecated]`.
// @summary: best-effort transpilation via mycelium-transpile (M-873). Declared,
// unvalidated ‚Äî no Mycelium parser/typechecker confirms this output; see the
// accompanying .gap.json for every construct this pass could not express.
nodule std.io;

// EXPLAIN (L2-B/DN-124): Declared co-include of batch-sibling type surface (homes: std.io.error) so single-file oracle is self-contained ‚Äî not a language `use` identity, not a short-form path collapse (M-1084 full path retained as provenance). Transitive type deps in the same batch are co-included. G2/VR-5.
type ByteCount = ByteCount(Binary{64});
type ByteOffset = ByteOffset(Binary{64});
type FieldPath = FieldPath(Bytes);
type IoError = UnexpectedEof(ByteCount) | Refused(Bytes) | EffectBudget(Bytes);
type SerError = Truncated(ByteOffset) | Malformed(ByteOffset, Bytes) | UnknownTag(FieldPath, Bytes) | OutOfDomain(FieldPath, Bytes) | BudgetExceeded(Bytes);
type ReadValueError = Io(IoError) | Ser(SerError);

// EXPLAIN (L2-B/DN-124): Declared co-include of batch-sibling type surface (homes: std.io.serialize) so single-file oracle is self-contained ‚Äî not a language `use` identity, not a short-form path collapse (M-1084 full path retained as provenance). Transitive type deps in the same batch are co-included. G2/VR-5.
type Format = Wire | Json;

// EXPLAIN (L2-B/DN-124): Declared co-include of batch-sibling type surface (homes: std.io.io) so single-file oracle is self-contained ‚Äî not a language `use` identity, not a short-form path collapse (M-1084 full path retained as provenance). Transitive type deps in the same batch are co-included. G2/VR-5.
type Budget = Bytes_kw(Binary{64}) | Unbounded;
type Sink = Sink(Vec[Binary{8}]);
type Substrate_kw = Substrate_kw(Vec[Binary{8}], Binary{64});
type Source = Source(Substrate_kw);
